abstract: A former football player, he spent three decades working for Walt Disney, his father-in-law, and had notable successes — until things turned sour.
snippet: A former football player, he spent three decades working for Walt Disney, his father-in-law, and had notable successes — until things turned sour.
lead_paragraph: Ron Miller, who rose through the ranks of his father-in-law’s entertainment company, Walt Disney Productions, but whose time as chief executive was tumultuous and ended with his ouster, died on Saturday at his home in Napa, Calif. He was 85.

abstract: Ralph Northam’s early life, growing up on Virginia’s rural Eastern Shore, provides clues about how his perspectives on race were shaped.
snippet: Ralph Northam’s early life, growing up on Virginia’s rural Eastern Shore, provides clues about how his perspectives on race were shaped.
lead_paragraph: ONANCOCK, Va. — When the United States Supreme Court ordered school districts in 1968 to dismantle their segregated classrooms, Wescott and Nancy Northam had a choice to make.

abstract: Whether he’s capturing David Lee Roth or Bed-Stuy street style, Montana Levi Blanco’s secret: an anthropological attention to detail and “amazing aggressive shopping.”
snippet: Whether he’s capturing David Lee Roth or Bed-Stuy street style, Montana Levi Blanco’s secret: an anthropological attention to detail and “amazing aggressive shopping.”
lead_paragraph: At Earrings Plaza, a Herald Square emporium devoted to all things bright, beautiful and cubic zirconium, the costume designer Montana Levi Blanco plucked a pair of feathery blue danglers from the hook. “Something with a tassel might be fun,” he said.

headline_main: A Costume Designer With Low Budgets and High Style
headline_print_headline: Working With Low Budgets but High Style

abstract: Music’s big awards show is trying to remedy its lack of diversity and heal a rift between the generations while remaining prime-time entertainment. It’s a tall order it hasn’t fulfilled yet.
snippet: Music’s big awards show is trying to remedy its lack of diversity and heal a rift between the generations while remaining prime-time entertainment. It’s a tall order it hasn’t fulfilled yet.
lead_paragraph: Year after year, I have dutifully watched the Grammy Awards. And the next morning, year after year, I have wondered why.

abstract: Every declared presidential candidate in the Senate voted against a bill that condemns the Trump administration’s plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan and Syria.
snippet: Every declared presidential candidate in the Senate voted against a bill that condemns the Trump administration’s plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan and Syria.
lead_paragraph: You don’t often see this in Washington: some of the most liberal candidates in the 2020 presidential field lining up with President Trump on foreign policy.

headline_main: 2020 Democrats Align With Trump on Syria and Afghanistan

abstract: The Senate approved a Middle East policy bill that rebukes President Trump’s troop withdrawals while backing Israel against a movement to boycott it.
snippet: The Senate approved a Middle East policy bill that rebukes President Trump’s troop withdrawals while backing Israel against a movement to boycott it.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate overwhelmingly approved a Middle East policy bill on Tuesday that included both a rebuke to President Trump over his withdrawal of troops from Syria and Afghanistan and a contested measure to allow state and municipal governments to punish companies that boycott, divest from or place sanctions on Israel.

abstract: The 68-to-23 vote marks the second time in two months that a Republican-led Senate has admonished the president on foreign policy.
snippet: The 68-to-23 vote marks the second time in two months that a Republican-led Senate has admonished the president on foreign policy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate, in a bipartisan rebuke to President Trump’s foreign policy, voted overwhelmingly to advance legislation drafted by the majority leader to express strong opposition to the president’s withdrawal of United States military forces from Syria and Afghanistan.

headline_main: Senate Rebukes Trump Over Troop Withdrawals From Syria and Afghanistan
headline_print_headline: President Draws Bipartisan Swipe From the Senate

abstract: A group of moderate Democrats, led by Joseph R. Biden and Michael Bloomberg, are thinking of challenging Trump. If too many centrists run, they could box each other out.
snippet: A group of moderate Democrats, led by Joseph R. Biden and Michael Bloomberg, are thinking of challenging Trump. If too many centrists run, they could box each other out.
lead_paragraph: Howard Schultz, the former Starbucks chief executive contemplating an independent run for president, stated it as a plain matter of fact: For someone with his views — a distinctly white-collar blend of conservative fiscal instincts and liberal social values — there is no suitable political party.
